1
00:01:47,230 --> 00:01:48,880
You got up early. Good conditions

2
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:54,870
People feel good when good things happen -Did you make up?

3
00:01:56,170 --> 00:02:00,280
How is your co-working with Yezi?

4
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:06,380
Sorry, I shouldn’t bring it up

5
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:14,300
But by now you should know that paper can’s hold fire for long, she will find out sooner or later

6
00:02:16,140 --> 00:02:19,880
Saying it out can only upset one more person

7
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:24,040
There are few things we can change

8
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:34,120
You know, in these years you are the block to yourself. You are the only one that can’t let go

9
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:42,940
Maybe you are right. But it’s still not time

10
00:02:46,460 --> 00:02:52,560
You know after that thing with Xinran, I finally understand

11
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:56,680
All woman wants is someone to rely on

12
00:02:56,900 --> 00:03:01,240
They will believe in us as long as we are brave enough to make the decision

13
00:03:02,460 --> 00:03:05,760
Hold it as long as you want, but you have to make the decision someday

14
00:03:17,980 --> 00:03:22,280
Do you think I’m the one that she can rely on?

15
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:34,800
I wonder where did that Xiang Zeyi go? The one that was brave to love and hate, that didn’t care about others’ thinking?

16
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:44,140
The further you go, the longer your shadow gets

17
00:03:53,020 --> 00:03:54,680
Can you leave you own shadow?

18
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:03,300
One more round

19
00:04:07,330 --> 00:04:12,410
[15.The further you go, the longer your shadow gets]

20
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:18,770
Shao’s invitation of their anniversary party has arrived to our company, are you coming? -Yes

21
00:04:20,220 --> 00:04:24,790
Who is your plus-one? -Who is it?

22
00:04:24,790 --> 00:04:27,860
Xiang Zeyi? -Xiang Hui

23
00:04:29,140 --> 00:04:34,350
You are not getting back together, are you? -Of course not

24
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:41,060
Xiang Zeyi, I mean Xiang Hui

25
00:04:41,510 --> 00:04:47,200
They say Xiang Hui is already the animate director in Shao’s company

26
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:50,840
He has operated several big programs and he did very well

27
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:53,190
He’s got a good reputation in the field

28
00:04:56,270 --> 00:05:03,180
So weird that our big Shige (senior fellow apprentice) has almost turned to a celebrity now

29
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:06,290
He must’ve gone abroad to study in these disappearing years

30
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:10,840
That’s why now he is back and becomes the legend in animation

31
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:42,040
What’s wrong?

32
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:16,480
Mr.Shao, your new AD is so good. He did well on those programs

33
00:08:16,740 --> 00:08:22,790
Do we have any chance to meet him in person today? -Sure you can see him

34
00:08:23,930 --> 00:08:28,270
They say he is only 30 years old. This young man is great

35
00:08:29,170 --> 00:08:37,410
Where did you get such a talent? -Xing, we don’t ask a hero where he comes from

36
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:44,140
Ability values the most to me, not other things. Cheers -Cheers

37
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:52,010
Excuse me for a while

38
00:08:54,350 --> 00:08:55,520
Mr.Shao

39
00:08:57,580 --> 00:09:00,900
You make a great couple -Don’t joke anymore, Mr.Shao

40
00:09:01,190 --> 00:09:10,400
You are the reason that I get to such a great party -Enjoy. Don’t hold tight, I only invited familiars here

41
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:18,020
I need to borrow Xiang Hui from you, people are curious about him

42
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:23,970
They can’t wait to meet our Director Xiang -Go ahead

43
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:27,210
Are you alright by yourself? -Of course

44
00:09:33,070 --> 00:09:34,290
Xing

45
00:09:40,970 --> 00:09:49,710
Is this that AD Mr.Xiang Hui? -We’ve heard so much about you. You look handsome too

46
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:55,990
Xiang Hui, these two gentlemen are in charge of our later programs

47
00:09:56,290 --> 00:10:06,250
We are depending on them -You are joking Mr.Shao. We can’t do anything without your organization

48
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:10,680
Cheers

49
00:10:15,060 --> 00:10:21,130
I wish we also have a talent like Mr.Xiang in our company

50
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:30,290
Mr.XIang feel free to come to me if Mr.Shao is treating you bad

51
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:36,590
Xing, are you trying to steal my man after minutes you met?

52
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:42,590
Mr.Xiang is young and talented, every company will love to hire him

53
00:10:45,050 --> 00:10:49,560
Fine, just drink

54
00:10:55,280 --> 00:11:03,230
Gentlemen let’s go meet other clients of other programs -OK -Please

55
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:22,310
Cheers -Nice to meet you -Nice working with you

56
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:38,400
Are you not used to the environment inside? -Too many people makes me uncomfortable

57
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:46,370
So I’m out to get some fresh air -First time when I was in a cocktail party

58
00:12:46,370 --> 00:12:51,180
I was too nervous to even pick up a glass of wine, let alone talking to people

59
00:12:53,350 --> 00:12:59,970
But I looked at your socializing before. You are not that little girl that got too nervous to speak on stage any more

60
00:13:02,690 --> 00:13:05,960
I thought I’d never fit in places like this

61
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:11,350
Maybe people all grow up and compromise

62
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:21,200
But I realize that it may be hard to compromise, but you also get something from it

63
00:13:21,830 --> 00:13:23,270
What did you get?

64
00:13:31,390 --> 00:13:32,920
Never getting drunk?

65
00:13:35,530 --> 00:13:37,560
Is this your first time watching me drink?

66
00:13:39,810 --> 00:13:44,430
No. I’ve seen it for many times -Many times

67
00:13:50,940 --> 00:13:52,400
Doctor.Lin

68
00:14:04,780 --> 00:14:08,090
Aunt -Sen come home for dinner tonight

69
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:18,510
I have a meeting tonight -Do you? Last time you need to work late and this time you have a meeting

70
00:14:18,510 --> 00:14:24,040
Why are you so busy lately? -Yes aunt, I’ve been busy lately -Fine

71
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:31,700
Remember to come if you have time, I’ll cook what you like for you -OK aunt

72
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,410
Xiang Hui

73
00:14:43,110 --> 00:14:44,160
Mr.Shao

74
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,490
There is something wrong with this storyboard

75
00:14:46,780 --> 00:14:51,970
The client asked to change the story and the colors of clothes in PPM (Pre-production meeting)

76
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:59,540
Mr.Shao, if we have to change the color, the color of characters won’t match that of backgrounds

77
00:14:59,770 --> 00:15:05,830
So I suggest that we don’t change it. Why don’t we offer our professional thoughts to them?

78
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:17,040
Why don’t you give me two products, one of your suggestions and one of clients’

79
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:19,440
I’ll let them to decide

80
00:15:22,340 --> 00:15:28,630
I’ve made the best one, why do you need the other one?

81
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:33,840
This is what our client asked. If we only present one plan to them,

82
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:36,470
they’ll think that we are not professional or careful enough

83
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:42,180
It’s also a challenge to our profession to offer two plans for them to choose

84
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:49,560
Just do it. I believe you can make it

85
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:45,490
What’s wrong?

86
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:48,910
Look for yourself

87
00:16:51,090 --> 00:16:52,370
Is there any problem with them?

88
00:16:53,540 --> 00:16:59,420
Any problem? Do you know how I was yelled at by those people of the publishing house?

89
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:01,240
Why?

90
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:12,470
Miss, we promised that new version of story will match their publishing theme of the season

91
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,590
The modern urban style

92
00:17:17,630 --> 00:17:22,030
These, why are you still presenting traditional ones?

93
00:17:24,020 --> 00:17:25,260
What are these?

94
00:17:27,290 --> 00:17:32,290
It’s not we that promised. I said no in that meeting

95
00:17:33,990 --> 00:17:39,710
But you said you’d change something to match their theme, that why I signed that contract

96
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:42,800
I also said that I’d carry on our studio’s style

97
00:17:46,030 --> 00:17:52,090
You are throwing me under the bus. What do I say to them?

98
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:56,880
And you just need to change one episode, what’s the big deal?

99
00:17:57,930 --> 00:18:05,490
What’s the big deal? Zhuzi, you do know how much personal style means to us

100
00:18:06,170 --> 00:18:12,710
If we have to change our persistence for market, what’s the point of our studio?

101
00:18:14,450 --> 00:18:19,340
Persistence

102
00:18:21,450 --> 00:18:28,640
When can you be realistic? Throw away your so-called persistence for a while and just live your life now

103
00:18:29,220 --> 00:18:34,310
I’m not saying anything else, Yezi, this month we moved into this new office

104
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:40,150
I threw up an idealistic exhibition for you. I cannot make ends meet now, my artist

105
00:18:41,130 --> 00:18:45,920
Do you still remember we also have to eat? Our staff are depending on us

106
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:52,570
Now the publishing house refused our products, you tell me what to do next

107
00:19:07,340 --> 00:19:18,210
Do you know how many people in this world can really make a living on their habits?

108
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:26,060
You are lucky enough to have this job and make a living

109
00:19:26,380 --> 00:19:31,450
But if we building up this studio is to compromise to reality, I might as well give it all up

110
00:19:32,220 --> 00:19:35,890
Artist are you seriously being mad at me about this?

111
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:46,980
People say I am careless and can’t measure things, but I am better than some stubborn selfish person

112
00:19:47,230 --> 00:19:51,250
I am stubborn, you rude and reckless person

113
00:19:51,540 --> 00:19:56,920
You are the one to talk. Have you thought about the studio? Have you thought about us?

114
00:19:57,220 --> 00:20:02,300
You will learn about consequences when this studio breaks apart

115
00:20:06,810 --> 00:20:08,130
What’s going on?

116
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:10,890
Are they fighting again?

117
00:20:11,220 --> 00:20:13,600
It’s more serious than the last ones

118
00:20:13,890 --> 00:20:16,840
Are you just stepping outside?

119
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:23,100
Take my work or we lose the contract -Why don’t you lose the contract with me too

120
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:30,330
No one is more important than your so-called persistence -Bosses, can you calm down a little

121
00:20:30,630 --> 00:20:37,160
Take your hand off me -Just talk it through -Sit down -Hang on, we are canceling the contract, who do you pick?

122
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:46,690
Sit down and talk -Choose your side -Just sit down

123
00:20:51,250 --> 00:21:04,580
Are you two having a divorce? -I’m old enough to be on my own

124
00:21:04,860 --> 00:21:12,620
Even court can’t help you, you have to make it through

125
00:21:12,870 --> 00:21:20,340
Couples always make up. There is nothing that can’t be settled

126
00:21:20,620 --> 00:21:23,300
Fine, I’ll have to live on with what I chose

127
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:29,330
That attitude is not bad

128
00:21:31,190 --> 00:21:36,310
Let’s call it even now -What to do with you two

129
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:38,880
Can you talk now?

130
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:47,100
Tell us, what happened?

131
00:21:50,730 --> 00:21:58,900
If we still can’t present what chief editor Yu asks, we are all done

132
00:21:59,990 --> 00:22:07,730
Tell me about it, my clients in advertising are so much harder to deal with than your editor

133
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:15,650
But we are running out of time and I worry -Then stop talking and start working

134
00:22:15,910 --> 00:22:24,390
We are all here -Right. Eight hands. Let’s get to work

135
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,390
Come here Xixi

136
00:22:30,280 --> 00:22:34,240
What are you doing standing there? Come back to work now

137
00:22:35,670 --> 00:22:43,960
Take two chairs here, Xixi -Sit -Show me these two drawings -You take this part

138
00:23:20,830 --> 00:23:24,870
That man used to be popular in our college -Really?

139
00:24:28,340 --> 00:24:29,710
How do you know that I live here?

140
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:50,170
You’ve been ignoring my calls and I can’t see you lately

141
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:53,840
I am worried about you

142
00:24:55,210 --> 00:24:56,760
Why?

143
00:24:58,790 --> 00:25:02,410
I worry if you are doing well -I’m doing well

144
00:25:04,620 --> 00:25:07,790
So well that I’ve forgotten about where I was for the past years

145
00:25:14,740 --> 00:25:16,410
That thing happened

146
00:25:19,370 --> 00:25:20,910
All because of me

147
00:25:24,650 --> 00:25:26,200
I wanted to help

148
00:25:28,590 --> 00:25:30,400
But you refused to see me

149
00:25:32,700 --> 00:25:34,850
Do you know how that made me feel?

150
00:25:39,020 --> 00:25:40,610
I just want to make up to you

151
00:25:44,290 --> 00:25:49,580
How do you want to help? How do you want to make up to me?

152
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:57,290
I could’ve had good times with the one I loved

153
00:25:59,810 --> 00:26:01,310
How about now?

154
00:26:02,580 --> 00:26:04,380
I have nothing

155
00:26:06,730 --> 00:26:09,660
I’m living in terror

156
00:26:11,240 --> 00:26:13,450
I’m trying to forget who I am

157
00:26:17,100 --> 00:26:22,760
You have no idea how I made through the past years in there

158
00:26:28,010 --> 00:26:29,490
What about Yezi?

159
00:26:33,290 --> 00:26:38,450
It’s unfair to her -And can this solve anything?

160
00:26:40,410 --> 00:26:42,290
I know it’s too late for me to say or do anything

161
00:26:48,650 --> 00:26:50,220
I just hope you can promise me one thing

162
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:56,280
What?

163
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:11,530
Take good care of Yezi for me

164
00:27:16,720 --> 00:27:18,060
Thanks

165
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:30,310
Xiang Zeyi

166
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:47,740
I’ve paid for my mistakes

167
00:29:54,130 --> 00:29:55,670
I have nothing to say with you

168
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:09,140
In fact

169
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:14,720
My heart breaks seeing you like this

170
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:18,740
I’ve been loving you for all these years

171
00:30:23,800 --> 00:30:32,960
I’ve given up on pushing relationships with you but really hope that you have a good life

172
00:30:33,800 --> 00:30:37,180
I hope you can start over

173
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:55,340
OK

174
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:01,640
Leave

175
00:31:02,060 --> 00:31:03,700
I don't want to see you again

176
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:44,820
Hello

177
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:47,300
You are up early

178
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:55,260
Are you used to the house yet? It belongs to an old friend of mine, he went abroad so you just keep living there

179
00:32:58,660 --> 00:33:05,360
There is no place that I can’t get used to. Thank you Daniao

180
00:33:06,300 --> 00:33:12,440
Brothers don’t say this. BTW don’t forget about Yezi’s exhibition

181
00:33:14,360 --> 00:33:15,520
I know

182
00:33:19,540 --> 00:33:25,280
And you -I know, I’ll keep it a secret

183
00:33:26,620 --> 00:33:28,900
Gotta go, bye
